The paper deals with algorithms and complexity theory for graph problems on classes of graphs with a geometric structure, such as map graphs and unit disk graphs. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), and Graph Theory (cs.GT). Among these, cs.DM and cs.CG are the most likely categories, as the paper deals with graph problems on geometric structures and uses decomposition theorems. The other categories are also relevant, as the paper deals with algorithmic complexity and parameterized algorithms.
